<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="498" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[811,1456,981,1867]" box="[813,916,981,1007]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[811,1456,981,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
The figures of 
<bibRefCitation author="LE CALVEZ Y." box="[974,1157,1012,1039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" pagination="401 - 419" refId="ref5004" refString="LE CALVEZ Y. 1966. - Contribution a l'etude des Foraminiferes de l'Oligocene inferieur (Sannoisien) dans le Bassin de Paris. Eclogae Geologicae Helvetiae 59 (1): 401 - 419." type="journal article" year="1966">Le Calvez (1966</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="LE CALVEZ Y." box="[1172,1229,1013,1039]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" refId="ref5040" refString="LE CALVEZ Y. 1970. - Contribution a l'etude des foraminiferes paleogenes du Bassin de Paris. Editions du Centre national pour la Recherche scientifique, Paris, 326 p." type="book" year="1970">1970</bibRefCitation>
) are inspired by the specimen of the collection on the Parisian Basin. Her figure published in 1966, which unfortunately is a drawing, appears to be identical to the picture published in 1970. The main difference with Reuss species is the presence of numerous pustules on the test. These pustules are not mentioned by Reuss in his description of the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[811,1456,981,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Dr F. Rögl believes that the Le Calvez species is not the one of Reuss (message to AP 2014).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[811,1456,981,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reuss" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[835,1039,1299,1325]" class="Globothalamea" family="Elphidiellidae" genus="Elphidiella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[835,1039,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Elphidiella minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quoted by 
<bibRefCitation author="REISER H." box="[1189,1383,1299,1326]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" refId="ref5732" refString="REISER H. 1987. - Die Foraminiferen der bayerischen Oligozan-Molasse. Systematik, Stratigraphie und Palaobathymetrie. Abhandlungen der Bayerischen Staatsamlung fur Palaontologie und historishe Geologie, vol. 16, 131 p." type="book" year="1987">Reiser (1987: 93)</bibRefCitation>
in the Oligocene and noteworthy in the Bavarian Chattian where it would be not rare. Unfortunately, it is not figured and the author only gives the Reuss reference. As for Miocene references, they probably always concern 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Allix" authorityYear="1913" box="[1223,1448,1427,1453]" class="Globothalamea" family="Elphidiidae" genus="Polystomella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="falunica">
<emphasis box="[1223,1448,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Polystomella falunica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[811,1456,981,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
Finally, many of all the illustrations since 1974 of the Oligocene “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reuss" authorityYear="1865" box="[908,1125,1491,1517]" class="Globothalamea" family="Elphidiidae" genus="Polystomella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[908,1125,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Polystomella minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” correspond to other species, perhaps pro parte to, 
<taxonomicName authority="Reuss, 1864" authorityName="Reuss" authorityYear="1864" box="[1054,1451,1523,1549]" class="Globothalamea" family="Elphidiidae" genus="Polystomella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="latidorsata">
<emphasis box="[1054,1305,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Polystomella latidorsata</emphasis>
Reuss, 1864
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[811,1456,981,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
Asides from the Ellis &amp; Messina catalogue (1940 and supplements), only two references (
<bibRefCitation author="HOSIUS A." box="[1214,1358,1586,1613]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" pagination="157 - 184" refId="ref4799" refString="HOSIUS A. 1895. - Beitrag zur Kenntniss der Foraminiferen-Fauna des Ober-Oligocans vom Doberg bei Bunde. Jahresbericht des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins zu Osnabruck 10 (2): 157 - 184." type="journal article" year="1895">Hosius 1895</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="BEUTLER K." pageId="3" pageNumber="498" pagination="176 - 199" refId="ref4243" refString="BEUTLER K. 1914. - Die Foraminiferen im Sternberger Gestein. Archiv des Vereins der Freunde der Naturgeschichte in Mecklenburg 68: 176 - 199." type="journal article" year="1914">Beutler 1914</bibRefCitation>
) are given with the number of pages but no indication of illustrations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[811,1456,981,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">In 1997, one of us (AP) evoked the problem of mixing both species.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[811,1456,981,1867]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
To conclude, we think that now it’s impossible to give a description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reuss" authorityYear="1865" box="[980,1197,1778,1804]" class="Globothalamea" family="Elphidiidae" genus="Polystomella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[980,1197,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Polystomella minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it would be necessary to examine samples from the Reuss localities to obtain topotypic specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
